  <description><![CDATA[<p>Situated on the shores of Lake Geneva, locally known as Lac Léman, and close to the foothills of the Chablais mountains, Evian is a famous spa town perfect for a relaxing break. It has attracted visitors from around the world since the medicinal properties of the water were discovered in 1789. The Lake, is surrounded by dramatic scenery and you can stroll along the pretty lakeshore or hike in the Chablais mountains behind the town. The Evian championship Golf Club offers one of the best and most beautiful courses to play in the world. Boat trips depart from the port and you can explore the medieval Yvoire, an authentic fishing village, bustling with artists and craftsmen and now listed as one of the most beautiful villages of France. Combine your trip to Evian with a stay in the beautiful mountain resort of Morzine, to experience the perfect mixture of adventure and peaceful relaxation.</p>]]></description>
