  <excursions><![CDATA[<p><strong>Pre-bookable</strong></p>
<p><strong>Annecy</strong> £48, full day, Friday<br />Discover the canals and beautiful historical buildings to see why Annecy is called the ‘Venice of the Alps’. Take a boat trip on the beautiful lake, browse the colourful market set at the foot of the magical chateau and explore the narrow streets and walkways.</p>
<p><strong>Chamonix</strong> £48, full day, Tuesday<br />A wonderful town with stunning vistas of Mont Blanc and its dramatic glaciers. Take a trip to the famous Aiguille du Midi or the Mer de Glace (pay locally).</p>
<p><strong>Book locally |</strong> Prices are shown for guidance only.</p>
<p><strong>Evian Historical</strong> <strong>Walk</strong> Easy 1½ hrs, €5, Wednesday morning<br />Take a tour of the beautiful town of Evian with a professional guide and learn about its history and culture.</p>
<p><strong>Jardin de l’Eau</strong> £8, half day, Wednesday to Sunday<br />Visit the Jardin de l’Eau de Pré Curieux (water garden), accessed by boat. The gardens show the various water-based ecosystems, discover the fauna and flora found in lakes, torrents, wetlands prairies and deltas.</p>
<p><strong>Boat trips</strong> to<strong> Montreux</strong>, <strong>Lausanne</strong> and <strong>Chateau de Chillon</strong></p>
<p><em>Please note that we act at all times as selling agent for the suppliers of activities &amp; excursions</em>.<br /><br /></p>]]></excursions>
